section.section:
"Aftercare services" include:
Medical care;
Psychiatric care;
Vocational and social rehabilitation;
Supportive housing; or
Case management services.

The aftercare plan shall include:
Diagnoses, including existing psychiatric, somatic, and dental diagnoses;
Treatment initiated;
Medications prescribed, their dosage schedules, the amount of each medication given to the individual on release, and the information necessary to help the individual to obtain the prescribed medication in the community in accordance with the aftercare plan;
Date of release;
Location of community placement;
Plan for continuing treatment; and
List of referrals indicated, including:
Public social services;
Legal aid;
Educational services;
Vocational services; and
Medical treatment other than mental health services.
